Apr 6 2008 	Coventry Motor Inn - FREE PARKING!	First and foremost, paying $40 plus dollars for parking per night is outlandish. This seems to be the average price for parking when staying in the SF area...That being said, parking is FREE at the Coventry Motor Inn!I was a bit skeptical at first seeing how the rates were quite low, but the reviews were high and thought why not take a chance and save some money in the process.The location is about .5 miles from the piers which is a brisk morning walk. SF has a very good public transportation system so utilize it during your stay. Once I arrived at the Inn, I parked and didn't touch my car until we departed. Don't even bother trying to find parking in SF...You either have to pay an enormous fee for valet, or park a mile away from your destination.On to the Inn...Location was great. Located about .3 miles from the famous crookedest street. It's on the same street (Lombard), so it's an easy walk up the hill. Restaurants, gas station, mini-marts were all located within a block or so from the Inn.Front desk could've been a bit friendlier upon arrival, but the agent was young and seemed to have worked a long shift, so no biggie. He was however quite helpful in giving us information on the bus and cable lines and also made some great restaurant suggestions.The rooms are pretty basic. No microwaves or refrigerators, but they did have the normal amenities such as hairdryer, iron and ironing board, TV, a/c, etc. Just a no frills room meant to be slept in. Not much of a view from the windows, but what do you expect in the middle of a city. Also, try to request a room near the back of the building as the front of the Inn seems to be on a fairly busy street. I’m not too sensitive to noise, but I thought it would be good advice nonetheless.The room was clean and well maintained. Bathroom seemed recently updated with nice countertops and hardware. Water pressure was good and hot water abundant. Sheets, pillows and bed were fine as well. Fresh and clean.All in all, it was a great value and the money that we saved staying here more then paid for the other expenses occurred such as having very nice dinners and some side shopping. I'd highly recommend it. Don't forget...free parking! We saved almost $120 alone on not having to pay for parking…that’s gas money on the way home..haha.	
